revision.text:
{{More citations needed | date = November 2016 }}{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Bhavatharini | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Bhavatharini Raja | birth_date = | alias = Bhavatharani, Bavatharini, Pavatharini, Bhavadharini, Bhavatha | origin = [[Tamil Nadu]], India | instrument = [[Vocals]] | genre = [[Playback singing]] | occupation = [[Playback singer]], [[Music Director]] | years_active = 1995–present | label = | associated_acts = | website = | current_members = | past_members = }}
'''Bhavatharani''' is an [[Tamil people|Indian Tamil]] [[Singing|singer]] and [[music director]]. She is the daughter of [[film composer]] [[Ilaiyaraaja]]<ref name="engagement">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2005/08/04/stories/2005080413000200.htm|title=Ilayaraja's daughter gets engaged|date=August 4, 2005|website=The Hindu|access-date=November 30, 2016}}</ref> and her brothers are the noted film composers [[Karthik Raja]] and [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]. She has mostly sung songs under the direction of her father and brothers. She was awarded the [[National Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer]] in 2000 for her rendition of the song "Mayil Pola Ponnu Onnu" from the film ''[[Bharathi (film)|Bharathi]]'', composed by her father Ilaiyaraaja.
==Career== Bhavatharini made her debut as a singer for ''[[Raasaiyya|Raasaiya]]''. Her song was a major hit. From then onward, she has sung in albums composed by her father and brothers.
She has also lent her voice in songs composed by [[Deva (music director)|Deva]] and [[Sirpy]].
In 2001, she won the [[National Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer|National Award]] for the song ''Mayil Pola Ponnu Onnu'' in the movie ''[[Bharathi (film)|Bharathi]]'' (the music director was [[Ilaiyaraaja|her father]]).
She turned music director for the 2002 film ''[[Mitr, My Friend]]'', directed by [[Revathi]], starring [[Shobhana]]. She then forayed into the [[Telugu film industry]] with ''[[Avunaa]]''. She has also composed music for ''[[Phir Milenge]]'', directed by Revathi, starring Shilpa Shetty, Abhishek Bachchan and Salman Khan. In June 2012, she was roped in to score the tunes for ''[[Vellachi]]'', a village-based project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tamil.filmibeat.com/news/vellachi-music-bhavatharani-160969.html|title='வெள்ளச்சி' படத்திற்கு இசையமைக்கிறார் பவதாரிணி!|last=Akilan|first=Mayura|date=September 6, 2012|website=FilmiBeat|language=Tamil|access-date=November 30, 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life== She is married to an [[advertising]] executive, R. Sabariraj, son of S.N. Ramachandran.<ref name="engagement" /> Ramachandran is a former [[journalist]] who went into [[publishing]] and started ''Kannan Advertising''.<ref name="engagement" /> Bhavatharani studied at Rosary Metric School in [[Chennai]], where she was a classmate of the famous singer Bhargavi.
==Notable Filmography== * 1984: ''My Dear Kuttichathan'' (Malayalam) * 1995 ''[[Raasaiyya]]'' * 1996 ''[[Alexander (1996 film)|Alexander]]'' * 1997 ''[[Thedinen Vanthathu]]'' * 1997 '' [[Karuvelam Pookkal]]'' * 1997: ''[[Kadhalukku Mariyadhai]]'' * 1998: ''[[Kaliyoonjal]]'' (Malayalam) * 2000: ''[[Bharathi (film)|Bharathi]]'' (National Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer) * 2001: ''[[Azhagi (2002 film)|Azhagi]]'' * 2001: ''[[Friends (2001 film)|Friends]]'' * 2005: ''[[Oru Naal Oru Kanavu]]'' * 2005: ''[[Ponmudipuzhayorathu]]'' (Malayalam) * 2006: ''[[Azhagai Irukkirai Bayamai Irukkirathu]]'' * 2006: ''[[Thaamirabharani]]'' * 2008: ''[[Uliyin Osai]]'' * 2008: ''Dhanam'' * 2009: ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]'' * 2010: ''[[Goa (film)|Goa]]'' * 2011: ''[[Mankatha]]'' * 2012: ''[[Gundello Godari]]'' (Telugu) * 2014: ''[[Anegan]]''
