'''Giuliana Berlinguer''' (23 November 1933 - 15 September 2014) was an Italian director, screenwriter, and novelist.

== Life and career ==
Born in [[Mantua]], Berlinguer studied at the [[Silvio d’Amico Academy of Dramatic Arts]], where she graduated in stage direction.<ref name=Grasso>Aldo Grasso, Massimo Scaglioni. ''Enciclopedia della Televisione''. Garzanti, Milano, 1996 – 2003. {{ISBN|881150466X}}.</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=È morta Giuliana Berlinguer, regista del mitico "Nero Wolfe"|url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/cinema/2014/09/15/news/morta_giuliana_berlinguer-95798484/|accessdate=11 August 2015|work=[[La Repubblica]]|date=15 September 2014}}</ref> She later focused on television, directing several [[RAI]] TV-movies and series, notably a successful 1969 ''Nero Wolfe'' miniseries starring [[Tino Buazzelli]] in [[Nero Wolfe|the title role]].<ref name=Grasso>Aldo Grasso, Massimo Scaglioni. ''Enciclopedia della Televisione''. Garzanti, Milano, 1996 – 2003. {{ISBN|881150466X}}.</ref>

In 1983 she directed the war-drama film ''[[Il disertore]]'', which was screened at the [[Venice Film Festival]].<ref name=Grasso>Aldo Grasso, Massimo Scaglioni. ''Enciclopedia della Televisione''. Garzanti, Milano, 1996 – 2003. {{ISBN|881150466X}}.</ref> She was the wife of [[Giovanni Berlinguer]],
the brother of [[Enrico Berlinguer]].

